<GUIClass name="CMUI_ToolbarShip" id="5c895553-d2b2-4756-8d16-2e266c62c71b">
    <superclass name="CMUI_Frame"/>
    <transient/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>Allows you to add a toolBar to a frame. 

myParent
######

The myParent is the app form. This allows you to have the mouse events local on the form. The form must have the following methods:

doBtnToolBarMouseUp
doBtnToolBarLoadButtons
doBtnToolBarBubbleHelp

Check this classes corresponding methods for parameters.

Button Indexes
##########

The myParent form calls the addButton to add buttons to the toolbar. One of the parameters passed in to this method is an index to clone myButton.
It is advised that these indexes are a constant on your form that, because it the above mouse event methods a button object is passed back and by checking the index you
will be able to tell which button was clicked.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="_usergui"/>
    <Constant name="SpaceIndex" id="e9572316-b3ee-41da-8b7f-e201472b8d5a">
        <source>100</source>
        <type name="Integer"/>
    </Constant>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="myButton" id="68cccc52-6444-4886-b5c4-21e476d07d78">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="CMUI_ToolbarShipButton"/>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="myCurrentTerminal" id="37355f26-b962-4448-b890-23b8b6d322af">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="CM_Terminal"/>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="myParent" id="d7eb3893-8395-4e0a-ac79-c084b0e851db">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Form"/>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <PrimAttribute name="offSet" id="48399598-4441-475b-a2d4-2a24d3ea32e7">
